Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @Riced Cauliflower{250%grams} and cook until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Season well with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm until serving.

Meanwhile, halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small chunks.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}.

Drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in another #large saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper chunks and cook, stirring, for ~{3%minutes}.

Add the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @Worcester Sauce{7.5%grams} to the pan. Cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Finely Chopped Tomatoes with Onion and Garlic{1%carton}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and mixed beans.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Soured Cream{75%grams} into a #small bowl{}.

Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Mix well.

Stir the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} into the stew a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the cauli rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the veggie stew, a dollop of soured cream and sprinkle over the cheese. Enjoy!

